The paper proposes a novel boosting approach that leverages proximal methods for optimization, which is particularly useful when the empirical risk to minimize is not differentiable. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper presents numerical experiments on simulated and real-world data, indicating that it may also be relevant to the data science (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories.
